content.description: On the right side of the Chaos wall, start standing left hand in a gaston pocket, and right hand on a good part of the arete out right.  Do a couple powerful bumps and a fun jump to the top.
content.protection: A couple pads, kind of a rock behind you, probably won't hit it though.

content.description: From east side of bluff walk south past project wall.  Head up to the rim of bluff and look for boulders laying on top of each other.  Climb out from the cave here is the project.  Pads and spotters needed for sure.
content.location: Walk through saddle, and head right (south).  Pass project wall and keep moving up bluff line.  You will see boulders laying on one another.  This is the cave.

content.description: Sit start on obvious edges and climb straight up the gently overhanging face.
Starts with left hand on the good sloped ledge and right hand in good slot/crimp.  Goes left hand to a decieving slopey sidepull. Then throw to a bomber slot/jug. Keep it together for the topout.
content.location: Southeast of saddle. Just below cave, past Chaos on the right.

content.description: Start on the sloping ledge and traverse to the left. From there make a bigger bump to a jug and use smaller holds to a sloppy mantle. Beautiful views, but a nervous punt could land you off the top of the bluff.
content.protection: 2 or 3 pads, and one hell of a committed spotter.
content.location: On top of the bluff facing parking lot and over looking Sawyer's Boulder.

content.description: Starts on descent holds and moves up into no-mans land with horrible feet.
content.location: Head past the saddle and turn right.  Problem is on steep face with a boulder right in front of it.  Chaos is to the left of this.

content.description: Just left of the Project.  Climb corner with fun features and good top-out.
content.location: Project wall, just left of the Project.

content.description: Start on two pockets on the right side of the face. Make a long throw up left to a good sidepull.  Traverse right to corner and topout straight up.
content.location: First boulder south of the project wall.

content.description: Start down and left on pockets.  Move up and right to the ledge, traverse right to corner and topout straight up.
content.location: First boulder south of the project wall.

content.description:
Great starter crack; takes cams, wired nuts, and hexes nicely.    There's an overhanging oak tree that aids in a top rope set-up to keep your rope off the rock. 

  Climb lower crack left of Cottonmouth and mount the large ledge, step around right and continue corner crack.  When the crack becomes too large for pro, finish the last ten feet on the right face.
content.protection: Mixed rack of hexes, wired nuts, and cams; top rope is an easy set-up.
content.location: Left corner from Cottonmouth; main cliff east. Approach up hill through boulders between Kutcher Bluff and Main bluff. See pictures.

content.description: First striking crack as you enter the climb up the east hill behind the main cliff; opposite side from Venom and Timber Rattler climbs.    Great crack to start the climb and then face and thin finger crack to finish the top section.
content.protection: Top rope or go with mixed cams and smaller nuts at the top.
content.location: Northeast side of main bluff; meander up the hill through the boulders and you meet the climb head-on.

content.description: Problem starts with a bomber ledge for feet off to the right of start hands. Thrutch out left to increasingly good crimps. From there head up to increasingly better holds to top out.
content.protection: pad on ground and one on rock directly behind you.
content.location: thru saddle. take a right and it is not far down on the right. It is apparently on the same wall and to the left of the 'project' i think.  It is also just before the 'dicey' problems and also 'jump for joy'

climbs.name: Can't hang
climbs.fa: T. Melin w/ old sausage fingers Forge.

content.description: Just up hill from Project.  Scramble up to large ledge, problem is tall featured face to the right.  Another really fun but tricky problem.  Holds have changed over the years, so I'm not sure on current conditions.
content.location: Backside of southern bluff, just up hill from project wall.

content.description: Lots of blood shed on this one from a number of folks.Start sitting, match in an undercling as for Hocus Pocus.  Trend right through the face, the crux probably being a hard shouldery move in the middle.  The end has a few methods to it, the easiest one for me used a knee bar.
content.location: On Chaos wall.  Walk road up to the saddle from the parking, hang a right and it’s at the base of the main cliff formation.Shady all day.

content.description: This is the east side of the main cliff.
